# Git sync — pull before work (MyWebsite)

When the user starts a work session (first message asking to implement, fix, edit, test, or continue project work), **pull from GitHub first** before making changes.

## What you must do

1. Run the sync-start script for the current OS **before** editing code or running project tasks.
2. Report the result briefly: up to date, pulled N commits, or pull failed.
3. If pull fails (conflicts, dirty state), stop and help resolve before continuing.
4. After a successful pull, **read** `Docs/SESSION_HANDOFF.md` and briefly report to the user: **From / When / Done / Next / Watch out** (skip empty sections). This is the Mac↔PC Cursor memo.

## Commands

**Windows** (work folder `D:\WebWork\MyWebsite`):

```bat
D:\WebWork\MyWebsite\scripts\sync-start.bat
```

**Mac** (work folder `~/Documents/MyWebsite`):

```bash
./scripts/sync-start.sh
```

Equivalent: `git pull --rebase` in the project root. Remote is GitHub `origin` (`giicha2/AIwebsite`).

## When to skip

- User explicitly says they already pulled, or only wants a question answered with no code changes.
- Conversation is clearly continuing the same session right after a successful pull in this chat.

## After pull

- Proceed with the user's task.
- Push at end of work per `git-sync-finish.mdc` (user says "올려줘" or after a substantial task, offer once).

## Paths (do not edit inside Synology Drive as the main workspace)

| Role | Windows | Mac |
|------|---------|-----|
| Work folder | `D:\WebWork\MyWebsite` | `~/Documents/MyWebsite` |
| Git origin | `https://github.com/giicha2/AIwebsite.git` | same |
| Drive folder | deploy/reference only — not the Cursor root | same |
